# ovh\_vps\_order\_rule\_datacenter (Data Source)

Use this data source to discover the datacenters available for a VPS plan prior to ordering it.

## Example Usage

```hcl
data "ovh_vps_order_rule_datacenter" "vps_le_1" {
  ovh_subsidiary = "US"
  plan_code      = "vps-le-1-2-20"
}
```

## Argument Reference

* `ovh_subsidiary` - (Required) The OVH subsidiary (e.g. `FR`, `US`, `CA`, `DE`, `GB`).
* `plan_code` - (Required) The plan code of the VPS to order.
* `os` - (Optional) Filter availability by OS family.

## Attributes Reference

* `datacenters` - List of datacenters where the plan can be ordered:
  * `code` - Short datacenter code.
  * `datacenter` - Full datacenter name.
  * `days_before_delivery` - Estimated number of days before delivery.
  * `status` - Overall availability status.
  * `linux_status` - Availability status for Linux.
  * `windows_status` - Availability status for Windows.
